NOTE: For now, the instructions for building csvn are a bit complicated
      because we haven't worked out all the kinks yet. Once we have done
      more testing on different platforms, it should be possible to build
      csvn without downloading ctypeslib or gccxml.

I. Building dependencies:

  1. Download and install the latest version of cmake (e.g. cmake 2.4.6)
     from http://www.cmake.org/HTML/Download.html

  2. Checkout and install the latest version of gccxml from CVS.

       $ cvs -d :pserver:anoncvs@www.gccxml.org:/cvsroot/GCC_XML login
       $ cvs -d :pserver:anoncvs@www.gccxml.org:/cvsroot/GCC_XML co gccxml
       $ cd gccxml
       $ mkdir gccxml-build
       $ cd gccxml-build
       $ cmake ../gccxml
       $ make
       $ make install

  3. Install Python 2.5

  4. Checkout and install the latest version of ctypeslib from svn.python.org:

       $ svn co http://svn.python.org/projects/ctypes/trunk/ctypeslib
       $ cd ctypeslib
       $ python setup.py build install

II. Building and testing csvn itself

  1. Build csvn/core/defines.py
       $ python generate-defines.py > csvn/core/defines.py

  2. Build csvn/core/functions.py
       $ python generate-functions.py

  3. Check that defines.py and functions.py have been built correctly.

       $ ls -l csvn/core

          -rw-r--r--  1 djames svnadmin  20587 Apr 14 22:54 defines.py
          -rw-r--r--  1 djames svnadmin 419460 Apr 14 22:54 functions.py
          -rw-r--r--  1 djames svnadmin   2044 Apr 12 23:00 functions.py.in
          -rw-r--r--  1 djames svnadmin   2523 Apr 12 23:04 __init__.py

  4. Run example.py and see whether it works. If it works, the output
     should look something like this:

       $ python example.py

       Repos UUID:  4419cd3e-282d-48c6-bf73-3fb589a7fb24
       Committed revision 1
       Committed revision 2
       Committed revision 3
       Committed revision 4
       Committed revision 5
       Committed revision 6

